senses
  entry
    definition "the subject matter of a conversation or discussion"
    examples ("he didn't want to discuss that subject" "it was a very sensitive topic" "his letters were always on the theme of love")
    id oewn-06612141-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (subject topic)
  entry
    definition "a unifying idea that is a recurrent element in literary or artistic work"
    examples ("it was the usual ‘boy gets girl’ theme")
    id oewn-05928866-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (motif)
  entry
    definition "(music) melodic subject of a musical composition"
    examples ("the theme is announced in the first measures" "the accompanist picked up the idea and elaborated it")
    id oewn-07042734-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("melodic theme" "musical theme" idea)
  entry
    definition "an essay (especially one written as an assignment)"
    examples ("he got an A on his composition")
    id oewn-06421395-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (composition paper report)
  entry
    definition "(linguistics) the form of a word after all affixes are removed"
    examples ("thematic vowels are part of the stem")
    id oewn-06311183-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (root "root word" base stem radical)
  entry
    definition "provide with a particular theme or motive"
    examples ("the restaurant often themes its menus")
    id oewn-02368596-v
    partOfSpeech v
